Spain Selects 6 Banks to Manage Sale of Power Bill-Backed Bonds

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-06-24T09:28:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/spain-selects-6-banks-to-manage-sale-of-power-bill-backed-bonds.html
Spain picked six banks to manage the
latest round of securities sales under its 22 billion-euro ($31
billion) power bond program, according to the Electricity
Deficit Amortization Fund, known as FADE.  The government selected  Banco Santander SA (SAN) ,  Citigroup Inc. (C) ,
 HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) ,  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ,  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  and
 Credit Agricole SA (ACA)  to handle the sale, according to a statement
